steps.description:
Draw a door outline on one part of the box or several doors on different boxes. A double door is best for stores. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/37/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/37/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut out the inner part of the doors. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/12/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/12/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cover with plastic to make them appear like glass doors. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a0/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a0/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For an external exit door, simply cut a rectangle on one side of the box and write EXIT over the top of it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/36/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/36/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut a large square for the base. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b2/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b2/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut a short rectangle that has the same length as the base and glue or tape it on the side. This will be the headboard. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut a rectangle with a width of about 2 inches/5cm and the same length of the headboard.This will go on top of the headboard, and if you like, make this wider, to be just above the end of the base. Get a piece of cardboard that reaches down to the end of the base and glue or tape it on to make a canopy. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/55/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/55/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Get some very short pieces of cardboard. Put them in the front and sides except for directly under the area on top of the headboard. For that part, get 2 little rectangles that reach from the area on top of the headboard to the base. You're done! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8d/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8d/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To really customize it, get an old tee or a shirt and cut out bedspread and pillows. To make pillows fluffy, get a rectangle of fabric, size of choice and get some cotton balls and arrange however you want. Now, fold it in half and staple or sew closed. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/db/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/db/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-10Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Paint or paper-cover the boxes to make them seem more homely. Cut out some windows on the outside of the house. Add curtains made from pieces of scrap fabric. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/82/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/82/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut out a door that goes between the rooms of the house. If you made the house upwards, add a staircase made from a concertina piece of card. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/69/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/69/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you can find paper with brickwork or wood on it, use this to cover the outside of the boxes. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Glue fake flowers to the sides of the house, to represent a garden. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/98/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/98/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-15Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

This will make the LPS house a home for the LPS pets. Here are just a few simple ideas:
Shelf: Use a square piece of cardboard and fold a tiny tab at the top. Glue the tab to the wall. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e4/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e4/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Bed: Use a rectangular piece of cardboard on top of a rectangular piece of foam or Styrofoam. Cover with scrap fabric to make a mattress. Add scrap fabric sheets and duvet, plus a pillow or two. Pillows can be made by wrapping fabric around cotton balls and gluing in place. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/74/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/74/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Computer: Fold a small piece of paper over a small wooden block or a square of thick cardboard. Cover with white paper. Draw a screen on the top. Make a rectangular piece of cardboard for the keyboard. Cover in white paper, then draw little keys onto it. For fun, use a small Lego or similar mouse as the computer "mouse". {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Rugs: Cut out rug images from magazines or print-outs; use scraps of fabric; use carpet offcuts, etc. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5b/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5b/Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Littlest-Pet-Shop-Building-Step-16Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
